/**
 * @addtogroup MIDILAR_Examples_CallbackHandler
 * @brief Practical examples showcasing callback abstraction with `CallbackHandler`.
 *
 * This group demonstrates how to use the `CallbackHandler<TArgs..., TResult>` class
 * for binding and invoking both standalone and instance-based functions in a platform-independent way.
 *
 * These examples are applicable to real-time embedded use (e.g., Arduino) as well as standard C++ builds.
 *
 * ---
 *
 * Each example demonstrates a different binding use case:
 *
 * - Standalone functions
 * - Instance methods
 * - Dynamic rebinding
 * - Null safety and invocation checks
 *
 * ---
 */
